SIMPLE: recount
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Recount
<hw>Re*count"</hw> <pr>(r⟦emac⟧*kount")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<ety>[Pref. <ets>re-</ets> + <ets>count</ets>.]</ety> <def>To count or
reckon again.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recount</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Recount
<hw>Re*count"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A counting again, as of
votes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recount</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Recount
<hw>Re*count"</hw> <pr>(r⟦esl⟧*kount")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>raconter</ets> to relate, to recount; pref. <ets>re-</ets> again +
<?/ (L. <ets>ad</ets>.) + <ets>conter</ets> to relate. See
<er>Count</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <def>To tell over; to relate in
detail; to recite; to tell or narrate the particulars of; to rehearse;
to enumerate; <as>as, to <ex>recount</ex> one's blessings</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To all his angels, who, with true applause,⟦br⟧
<qex>Recount</qex> his praises.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recountment</ent>⟦br⟧
